gomodel:SYNGO_892  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CHMP2B is found in dendritic shafts and spines where it colocalizes with PSD-95 as observed using confocal microscopy. Immunogold EM revealed significantly increased immunoreactivity in spines, where particles arranged beneath the spine membrane around the PSD. Subcellular fractionation revealed enrichment in membranes and synaptoneurosomes and PSD fractions, but could be solubilized from the PSD fraction by using Sarkosyl. Immunoprecipitation of CHMP2B from synaptoneurosomes also precipitates PSD scaffolds and this was also confirmed by mass spectrometry.. Experimental description: M&M:\n-Pregnant Oncins France souche A (OFA; a substrain of Sprague Dawley) rats (Charles River) were used for primary neuron cultures, and 2-month-old OFA rats of both sexes were used for biochemical analysis of brain tissue.\n-Three-month-old male C57BL/6 mice and 1.3-month-old female Chmp2b KO mice(here called KD mice since knock-out is incomplete; Ghazi-Noori et al., 2012) or female WT littermates (on C57BL/6 background) were used for immunohistochemistry and electron microscopy (EM) studies.\n- From Belly et al., 2010, where shRNA was described: The shRNA targeted the rat CHMP2B sequence at positions 578-596 (5 - GACACTACAAACAATGCAG-3 ) according to Lee et al. (Lee et al., 2007) and the encoding oligonucleotide was cloned between the HindIII and BglII sites of pSuper- mCherry." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_892" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

